The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to analyze large datasets in psychology, which suggests that it belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on the development of a methodology for working with large datasets, which could fall under the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category. The study also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it deals with human moral decision-making. Finally, the paper discusses the identification and validation of moral phenomena, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
